    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - FULLER 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS - DISASSEMBLE - SHIFT LEVER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="2">
        <title>SHIFT LEVER</title>
        <figure id="f1303275" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303275.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 75. Shift Lever Disassembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1303275">Figure 75</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">On a non-isolated shift lever, remove the shift knob. If the shift lever is equipped with a
                lever isolator, remove the snap ring, bushing, and cross pin to disconnect and remove the upper lever.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the rubber boot up and off the shift lever shaft.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Secure the assembly in a vise with the housing bottom facing up.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a large screwdriver to twist between the spring and housing, forcing the spring from
                under the housing lugs. Release the spring one coil at a time
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303276">(Figure 76).</hotlnk>
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1303276" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303276.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 76. Remove Springs</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the tension spring, washer, and gear shift lever from inside the housing tower.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the spade pin.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the O-ring.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
